metatags.title: Jack Horner: Building a dinosaur from a chicken  | Video on TED.com
metatags.og:title: Jack Horner: Building a dinosaur from a chicken  | Video on TED.com
metatags.og:description: TED Talks Renowned paleontologist Jack Horner has spent his career trying to reconstruct a dinosaur. He's found fossils with extraordinarily well-preserved blood vessels and soft tissues, but never intact DNA. So, in a new approach, he's taking living descendants of the dinosaur (chickens) and genetically engineering them to reactivate ancestral traits — including teeth, tails, and even hands — to make a "Chickenosaurus".
